The following document gives an overview of the available actions on jobs in the Batch Jobs portal.

## Creating a new job
It is possible to create a job directly from the Batch Jobs portal. Custom parameters can be configured for the job and used as attributes in the [Transform Files (DT)](/doxee-platform/docs/transform-files-dt-batch-workflow-task-reference), [Compose Documents (DC)](/doxee-platform/docs/compose-documents-dc-batch-workflow-task-reference) and [Produce Indexes (OM)](/doxee-platform/docs/produce-indexes-om-batch-workflow-task-reference) Batch Workflows tasks.

- Click **Create job **on the toolbar. A pop-up window is shown:

![](data:image/png;base64,)	

- Select the **Account **for which to create the new job. Start typing the name of the account to filter the list.

- Select the required Batch **Workflow **resource. Start typing the name of the workflow to filter the list.

- Select the **Release **of the Batch **Workflow **resource to use.

- Select the input **File **to upload.

- In the **Parameters **field, click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Add **to add a new parameter.

> Note

The maximum number of parameters for a job is 10.

> Note

Configured parameters can be viewed in the job logs.

Enter a **Key**.

> Note

The maximum character length is 50. 

Each Key must be unique within its job.

The BOM parameter Key must not contain blank spaces.

- Enter a **Value**.

> Note

The maximum character length is 50.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) to confirm the parameter.

- Click **Create**. The new batch job is now visible in the **Jobs **table.

> Note

The **Create job **button is only enabled if no jobs are selected.

## Managing jobs
Select one or more jobs to view the available actions, for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

Actions that are available on individual files may not be available on a multiple selection (for example the **Inspect **action).

**Scope**

**Icon**

**Action**

**Description**

**Production**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Interrupt production**

Stop the execution of the job. The current production steps will be interrupted. 

> Note

This action is only available for jobs in **Production in progress **status.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

** **[**Resume production**](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-jobs#resuming-production)

Resume the production steps of the job. Only the tasks that failed will be restarted, preserving what was has already been executed successfully.

> Note

This action is only available for jobs in **Production interrupted **status.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

** **[**Restart production**](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-jobs#restarting-production)

Restart the production steps of the job.

> Note

This action is only available for jobs in **Production interrupted **status.

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Cancel production**

Cancel the production steps currently in progress.

> Warning

Canceled jobs cannot be recovered.

> Note

This action is only available for jobs in **Production interrupted **status.

**Delivery**

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[**Approve delivery**](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-jobs#approving-delivery)

Approve delivery so that the job can continue with its next processing steps.

> Note

This action is only available for jobs in **Delivery approval **status.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

**Interrupt delivery**

Stop the execution of the job. The current delivery steps will be interrupted. 

> Note

This action is only available for jobs in **Delivery in progress **status.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

** **[**Resume delivery**](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-managing-jobs#resuming-delivery)

Resume the delivery steps of the job.

> Note

This action is only available for jobs in **Delivery interrupted **status.

> Important

To resume sending emails, PEC emails and SMS messages correctly, avoiding duplicates, the **Analytics **option must be enabled for the workflow. For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Batch Workflows - Editor](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-workflows-editor).

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

**Cancel delivery**

Cancel the delivery steps currently in progress.

> Warning

Canceled jobs cannot be recovered.

> Note

This action is only available for jobs in **Delivery approval **or **Delivery interrupted **status.

> Tip

You may also hover on the name of a job, click on the **... **icon that appears, and select one of the available actions from the context menu. For example:![](data:image/png;base64,)

### Approving delivery
- Select a job that has stopped and is awaiting manual approval; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Approve delivery**).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Approve **to confirm. The job will now proceed to the delivery steps for all the produced outputs.

### Resuming production
- Select a job whose production steps were not completed successfully, for which you want to restart only the tasks that failed.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Recover production**).

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Select the **Release **of the resources to use:

**Current**: the release currently used by this job execution

- **Active**: the currently deployed release

- **Custom**: select a specific release from the list of available ones; for example:

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- *(optional) *Activate the **Force relaxed mode **toggle to resume production and execute the failed Document Composition and Data Transformation tasks in relaxed mode.

> Note

This toggle is only available if the job contains, and failed on, one of these tasks:

[Compose Documents (DC)](/doxee-platform/docs/compose-documents-dc-batch-workflow-task-reference) 

- [Count Pages (DC)](/doxee-platform/docs/count-pages-dc-batch-workflow-task-reference-1) 

- [Transform Files (DT)](/doxee-platform/docs/transform-files-dt-batch-workflow-task-reference)

If the job failed on a different task, this toggle will not be available.

- *(optional) *Add a comment which will be visible in the job details.

- Click **Confirm **to proceed. Only the tasks that failed will be restarted, preserving what was has already been executed successfully.

### Restarting production
- Select a job whose production steps were not completed successfully, and that you want to restart from the beginning.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Restart production**).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Select the **Release **of the resources to use:

**Current**: the release currently used by this job execution

- **Active**: the currently deployed release

- **Custom**: select a specific release from the list of available ones

- Click **Confirm **to proceed. The job and all its tasks will be restarted from the beginning.

### Resuming delivery
- Select a job whose delivery steps were not completed successfully.

- Click ![](data:image/png;base64,)  (**Recover delivery**).

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Resume **to confirm. Only the tasks that failed will be resumed, keeping track of what was has already been delivered successfully.

> Important

To resume sending emails, PEC emails and SMS messages correctly, avoiding duplicates, the **Analytics **option must be enabled for the workflow. For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Batch Workflows - Editor](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-workflows-editor).

### Downloading input or output files
- Select a job.

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Download inputs**, or **Download content**) to save a copy of the corresponding input (or, respectively, output) files to your local filesystem.

> Note

The job's input (or output) files are downloaded in ZIP format; for example: *job-12499.inputs.zip *(or *job-12499.content.zip*).

> **Data retention period**

If the job is older than the configured data retention period of the tenant, the job files will automatically be removed from the system. The job details will still be visible in the Batch Jobs portal, but the **Download **buttons will be disabled and a warning shown.

### Downloading logs
- Select a job.

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Download logs**) to save the job's log files to your local filesystem.

> Note

The job's logs are downloaded in plain text format; for example: *job-12499.logs.txt*.

> Important

If the job's logs are not ready yet, the system displays a notification message instead of downloading an empty file.

### Adding labels
It is possible to add one or more labels to a job, which will be visible in the Jobs tab of Batch Jobs, the details panel of the job, and the job's log. Jobs may also be searched and filtered through their labels.

> Note

Adding, reordering or removing labels is only available to users with a specific permission.

- Select a job.

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) **Assign labels**. A pop-up window is opened:

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,)    **Add **to add a label. Enter a label name and press *Enter *to save it.

> Note

Only letters (A-Z, a-z), numbers (0-9), underscores (_) and hyphens (-) are allowed. The label name must start with a letter or number. The maximum number of characters is 100.

The maximum number of labels added to a job is 5.

> Tip

It is possible to insert hyperlinks as labels. The link will be clickable in the Jobs table and details panel.

> Important

If more than one job has been selected, only new labels can be appended to the selection. Existing labels for the selected jobs cannot be reordered or removed.

- Change the order of labels by dragging and dropping them to the desired position.

- Remove a label by clicking  ![](data:image/png;base64,) .

> Tip

To search for jobs without labels, select the **Label **filter in the search bar and enter the string "No Notes" (case-sensitive).

### Inspecting a job
The **Inspect **panel provides more information on the status and properties of the selected job, including details on the individual job steps and on the corresponding input file.

- Select a job.

- Click  ![](data:image/png;base64,) (**Inspect**), or click on the name of the job.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

> Note

For more information, see: [Doxee Platform Batch Jobs - Inspect Panel](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-inspect-panel), section "Inspecting a job".

## Status housekeeping
If a job remains in an unresolved status for a certain period of time, it will be automatically transitioned into a final status. This is an optional system configuration to prevent the accumulation of unresolved jobs.

The status change is recorded in the job history of the details panel (see [Viewing the details of a job](/doxee-platform/docs/doxee-platform-batch-jobs-user-manual#viewing-the-details-of-a-job)).

The table below lists the unresolved states in which a job may be stuck and their corresponding final states:

**Unresolved status**

**Final status (set by housekeeping service)**

![](data:image/png;base64,) Production cancelled

![](data:image/png;base64,) Delivery in approval

![](data:image/png;base64,) Delivery cancelled

![](data:image/png;base64,) Delivery interrupted
